      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"it doesn't have to come from you.\" that's actually the first thing that has made sense today. i'm just tired of being forced to pretend that i have to carry this or that i have to contribute to a future that isn't even happening. if the world is just going to burn anyway, why is there this constant pressure to keep fighting to stay in it? it feels like everyone is just clinging to a sinking ship out of fear, but maybe there's more peace in just accepting that it's over.",
